<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pringle</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March 10,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>U. S. consul at Tegucigalpa telegraphs that Americans who fought with
                            Vasquez are threatened with expulsion by President Bonilla. Consul
                            Peterson urges my going there on the <hi rend="italic">Ranger</hi>.
                            Future complications might be avoided by a strong protest.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>